57 b. Ongoing communication with foster parents and
58 custodians, including review of reports prepared by foster
59 parents in the exercise of their right to be heard.
60 c. Personally review Department of Human Resources
61 court reports, Court Appointed Special Advocate reports,
62 Individualized Education Plans, Individualized Service Plan
63 reports, foster parent reports, and other information related
64 to the child including educational records, medical records,
65 mental health records, and any other relevant records
66 pertaining to the child.
67 (2) Attend and participate in the development and
68 negotiation of individualized service plans and proposed court
69 orders.
70 (3) Conduct an ongoing review of the progress of the
71 court case to promote the best interests of the child and to
72 promote a timely and permanent resolution to the case. Ongoing
73 review includes conducting monitoring of timely implementation
74 of individualized service plans and timely compliance with
75 court orders. When appropriate, the guardian ad litem shall
76 file pleadings with the court while the case is pending to
77 notify the court of delays and noncompliance.
78 (4)(3) Advocate for appropriate services for the child
79 and the family, which may include, but not be limited to,
80 trauma informed counseling for the child and trauma informed
81 training and ongoing coaching for the legal parents,
82 appropriate family members, and the foster parents.
83 (5)(4) Attend and be prepared to fully participate in
84 all dependencyjuvenile court hearings scheduled by the
