85 juvenile court, including examination and cross-examination of
86 witnesses, issuance of subpoenas, offering of testimony,
87 seeking discovery when appropriate, and filing and file all
88 necessary pleadings to facilitate promote the best interests
89 of the child and timely, permanent resolution of the case.
90 Additionally, the guardian ad litem shall obtain copies of all
91 relevant proceedings and notices and participate in
92 depositions and negotiations.
93 (d)(c) Before being appointed by the juvenile court,
94 every guardian ad litem appointed in juvenile dependency or
95 termination of parental rights cases shall receive training
96 appropriate to their role.
97 (e)(d) Nothing in this section shall prohibit the
98 juvenile court from appointing trained volunteers in addition
99 to guardians ad litem in promoting the best interests of the
100 child.
101 (f)(e) A guardian ad litem may be appointed to protect
102 the best interests of more than one child of the same parent.
103 A guardian ad litem also may be appointed to protect the best
104 interests of both a minor (or otherwise incapacitated) parent
105 and the child."
106 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
